            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "New York lawmakers passed a bill last week limiting a recently enacted law designed to shield nursing home CEOs from lawsuits during the coronavirus pandemic. The move followed a TMI reporting series spotlighting how New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo and Democratic legislators created the original legal immunity statute amid a flood of campaign cash from a health care industry lobby group that claimed to have drafted the provision.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Cuomo has not yet said whether he will sign the bill, though he has ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "said",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
